WEBVTT

00:01.058 --> 00:02.700
Hey there and welcome to Soul Church.

00:03.301 --> 00:07.106
Our prayer is that this message encourages you wherever you may be in life.

00:07.706 --> 00:12.712
We've been hearing so many stories about what God is doing in people's lives and we'd love to hear yours.

00:13.053 --> 00:17.579
So take a second and send your story to stories at soulchurch.com.

00:17.599 --> 00:21.644
Thanks again for joining us today and we hope that you enjoy the message.

00:22.064 --> 00:22.565
God bless.

00:24.487 --> 00:25.568
Well, so good to see you.

00:25.809 --> 00:30.034
Father, just as we receive your word today, fill us again.

00:30.466 --> 00:33.009
fill us up to send us out.

00:33.029 --> 00:34.992
We don't just want to gather, we want to go.

00:35.833 --> 00:40.799
So we thank you that you're going to equip the saints today to go into all the world.

00:40.819 --> 00:43.442
On mission in Jesus' name.

00:43.462 --> 00:43.822
Amen.

00:44.143 --> 00:44.423
Amen.

00:44.443 --> 00:50.450
Would you thank the worship team, all of our volunteers, those who serve us.

00:50.490 --> 00:53.574
Week in, week out, we appreciate you, we value you.

00:53.814 --> 00:56.418
Why don't you find your seats?

00:56.438 --> 01:00.082
I saw the new bus arrive with all the students from the UEA and

01:00.194 --> 01:01.135
The art college.

01:02.056 --> 01:02.696
It looked packed.

01:02.717 --> 01:04.138
Come on, let's thank all of our students.

01:04.158 --> 01:05.239
So great to have you here.

01:11.605 --> 01:12.867
Study hard, pray hard.

01:12.887 --> 01:13.627
You should be all right.

01:15.009 --> 01:16.410
How good was Pete Greg last week?

01:17.771 --> 01:18.332
I loved it.

01:20.975 --> 01:22.516
I loved that thought about omission.

01:23.437 --> 01:24.318
Jesus said, go.

01:24.358 --> 01:25.479
And then he said, stay.

01:27.241 --> 01:27.962
Wait and pray.

01:27.982 --> 01:28.402
And then

01:28.546 --> 01:29.548
go into all the world.

01:29.668 --> 01:30.530
I just loved it.

01:30.550 --> 01:34.657
I've been with Pete this week at a conference and he was stirring us up again to pray.

01:35.178 --> 01:38.544
We've got a fresh stirring after last week to pray and seek God.

01:38.564 --> 01:39.165
I know we did.

01:39.766 --> 01:41.009
He said this.

01:41.049 --> 01:44.615
He says, prayer is the ignition for the great commission.

01:45.176 --> 01:46.298
Prayer is the ignition.

01:46.819 --> 01:47.781
And I was stirred.

01:48.142 --> 01:52.690
Week one, we launched our mission mandate, which is therefore go.

01:52.802 --> 01:59.373
and make disciples of all nations baptizing them in the name of the Father, the Son and the Holy Spirit.

01:59.393 --> 02:01.056
That's our mandate for the year.

02:01.076 --> 02:02.759
And we looked at those three thoughts.

02:02.919 --> 02:05.143
Our mission begins with vision.

02:05.443 --> 02:07.707
We cannot reach what we don't see.

02:08.228 --> 02:15.239
God, open our eyes to see those on this journey who are lost, who are in need of a Savior.

02:15.780 --> 02:19.186
And as I prayed, we don't just want to gather, we want to go.

02:20.002 --> 02:25.370
So for so long, the church on a hall is just gathered and we haven't had this mandate to go.

02:25.410 --> 02:30.056
But this year, the mandate is to go into all the world and bring the gospel.

02:31.739 --> 02:38.168
Our second mandate was our mission is to focus on what's lost, not just on what's found.

02:38.588 --> 02:42.013
God loves what's been found, but he's obsessed with what is lost.

02:43.055 --> 02:45.298
We talked about the remote control in the couch.

02:45.922 --> 02:51.089
When you're looking for the remote control, you are obsessed with the remote, but you still love the couch.

02:52.851 --> 02:59.219
Sometimes in church, we get obsessed with the couch when actually the remote is lost, people are lost.

02:59.820 --> 03:05.608
And so instead of looking inward this year, we are looking outward as Christ commanded us.

03:06.288 --> 03:08.591
Thirdly, our mission requires action.

03:09.433 --> 03:13.618
2026 is love in action, which is the mission statement

03:13.986 --> 03:14.847
of soul church.

03:15.067 --> 03:17.590
Now we're going to hand out a card to you, okay?

03:17.610 --> 03:28.784
We're going to, two sides, and we're going to ask our amazing host team to servers with these cards, and on the front of the card, I want you to keep this safe the next 11 months, okay?

03:28.804 --> 03:37.074
On the front is our mission mandate, which we talked about already, and on the back is a prayer that I've written

03:37.570 --> 03:39.753
And we're gonna come onto that at the end, okay?

03:39.813 --> 03:40.894
So you don't need to do anything.

03:40.914 --> 03:43.678
You can just leave this in your hand, hold it in your Bible.

03:44.039 --> 03:53.091
But a part of the prayer is there is a space where I would love you to think about a name or one, two, three, four names, how many names you wanna place in there.

03:53.692 --> 03:57.737
And you can think about whose name is gonna go in that prayer.

03:57.817 --> 04:02.503
So as we hand those out, I also wanna ask you to do one more thing today.

04:02.543 --> 04:06.188
And I also wanna welcome those who are joining us online.

04:06.228 --> 04:07.410
Great to have you.

04:07.586 --> 04:11.370
journey on mission with us, drop as a message in the chat where you're watching from.

04:11.410 --> 04:14.533
If you need prayer and support at any point, our people are here.

04:15.274 --> 04:20.240
And if you don't support Nauru City, you should support Nauru City because we are going back where we belong.

04:20.480 --> 04:21.721
And you heard it first here.

04:22.142 --> 04:22.442
Who knows?

04:22.462 --> 04:24.264
You've got to keep looking up, not looking down.

04:24.925 --> 04:26.566
Okay, so I'm just putting it out there.

04:28.088 --> 04:29.950
So I'm asking you today to take notes.

04:30.290 --> 04:37.458
Okay, I'm going to encourage you to take notes, whether it's on your phone, on your, on your, whatever, your tablet,

04:38.402 --> 04:40.104
pen and paper if anyone remembers what that is.

04:42.346 --> 04:43.647
This is an important message.

04:45.669 --> 04:48.251
Now, our vision for the year is on mission.

04:48.451 --> 04:52.075
If you haven't picked that up yet, you will, okay?

04:52.095 --> 04:54.978
And that sounds good.

04:55.018 --> 04:56.039
The wristbands are cool.

04:56.059 --> 04:56.879
They glow in the dark.

04:57.040 --> 04:59.001
Give us a wave if you've got a wristband on, okay?

04:59.021 --> 05:01.424
If you haven't got one, we have some of the info desk.

05:01.444 --> 05:02.725
We want to make sure you get ahold of those.

05:03.365 --> 05:05.768
And last week, Pete was brilliant.

05:05.788 --> 05:08.210
It was fun, especially his elevator story.

05:09.730 --> 05:14.016
But the question I have is this, and I want to pitch it to us, why?

05:15.078 --> 05:16.419
Why do we have to go on mission?

05:17.942 --> 05:19.103
Why do we have to go on mission?

05:19.143 --> 05:23.650
We live in a generation, especially Gen Z and Gen Alpha, where they demand a why.

05:24.711 --> 05:27.535
I grew up in a generation, someone asked you to do something, he said, all right.

05:29.338 --> 05:32.562
Now they're like, no, not until you tell me why.

05:33.026 --> 05:35.769
And I think that's a good thing to know the why behind the mission.

05:35.829 --> 05:37.010
Why are we wearing the wristbands?

05:37.050 --> 05:38.571
Why are we giving out the handouts?

05:38.611 --> 05:40.113
Why are we encouraging the church?

05:40.133 --> 05:40.713
We're on mission.

05:41.314 --> 05:43.696
And so the why is the key to the mission.

05:44.497 --> 05:50.223
The why keeps you going when you want to quit and the why keeps you focused on the mission.

05:50.903 --> 05:59.011
And imagine being in the army or the navy or the Air Force and you're sent on a mission, but you don't know the why.

05:59.632 --> 06:01.874
Who knows the why gives you perspective to the mission?

06:02.498 --> 06:04.301
And Jesus was the master at the why.

06:04.842 --> 06:06.165
He always gave the why.

06:06.225 --> 06:12.256
And so for many of you, you know the why, you know the why we're on mission, but for others of you, you don't know the why.

06:12.476 --> 06:17.585
But I think for the majority of us today, we need to be reminded of the why.

06:18.487 --> 06:19.449
Why we're on mission.

06:19.970 --> 06:22.594
I don't know about you, but I can so get caught up in my world.

06:23.436 --> 06:24.658
Who's got their own little world?

06:25.762 --> 06:30.229
It's called your spouse if you're married, it's called your kids, it's called the school, it's called work.

06:30.269 --> 06:32.232
And we get caught up in our own little world.

06:32.492 --> 06:35.377
And before you know, like, Shantos is because where did a week go?

06:35.757 --> 06:37.741
Does anyone ever have that, like, where did that week go?

06:38.021 --> 06:40.685
Because we all get caught up in our own little worlds, okay?

06:40.705 --> 06:42.408
So that's normal, but it's important.

06:42.428 --> 06:46.654
So my message is titled today, why on mission matters?

06:47.436 --> 06:48.217
Why we're on mission?

06:48.878 --> 06:54.226
And we'll get to the how in a couple of weeks, but today it's critical because it's the why.

06:54.786 --> 06:56.688
So I want to share what I want to share today.

06:56.708 --> 06:58.069
I pray it comes with clarity.

06:58.209 --> 06:59.591
I pray it comes from compassion.

06:59.931 --> 07:01.132
I pray it comes with grace.

07:01.633 --> 07:05.316
And there's no fear mungering in some of the things I'm going to say because it's really important.

07:05.817 --> 07:14.445
And I want you to think about the space on the mission mandate on the prayer on the back of somebody that God is sending you on mission to reach this year.

07:15.085 --> 07:15.366
Okay?

07:15.386 --> 07:17.187
So I want you to be thinking about that as we go.

07:17.207 --> 07:18.889
And at the end, we're going to fill that in.

07:19.089 --> 07:21.251
We're going to give you some pens and we're going to pray.

07:22.312 --> 07:24.114
And every day over the next 11 months,

07:24.290 --> 07:34.781
I want you to pray the prayer, which is on the back of that mandate and believe God that somebody is going to find Christ this year in your world.

07:36.063 --> 07:37.464
Acts chapter two, verse 42.

07:38.285 --> 07:46.594
Every day, the reason I've written a prayer is because in Acts 2, 42, which is what Pete spoke about last week, he says, they devoted themselves to prayer.

07:47.475 --> 07:50.098
I want us to devote ourselves to prayer.

07:50.530 --> 08:01.342
So many times we devote ourselves to gossip, we devote ourselves to all sorts of negative things, but the early church saw a great revival because they devoted themselves to prayer.

08:01.782 --> 08:05.346
And so that prayer on the back of the Mander is gonna help us devote ourselves.

08:05.727 --> 08:07.269
We're gonna pray it together at the end.

08:07.309 --> 08:14.837
But before we do, I wanna share three really challenging, thought-provoking thoughts on why on mission matters.

08:15.197 --> 08:16.258
Why on mission matters?

08:17.340 --> 08:19.442
This is the first thought I want you to write down.

08:20.706 --> 08:24.952
Everyone is waiting to discover they're someone.

08:27.275 --> 08:32.222
Everyone is someone and everyone is precious to Jesus.

08:33.704 --> 08:40.433
Romans chapter five verse eight, but God demonstrates his own love for us in this.

08:41.195 --> 08:47.163
While we were still sinners, Christ died for us.

08:48.585 --> 08:49.426
Write this down.

08:49.794 --> 08:55.441
Everyone on earth is someone Christ died for.

08:55.461 --> 08:55.862
Everyone.

08:56.422 --> 08:58.225
Everyone on earth is someone Christ died for.

08:58.745 --> 09:05.914
Before we changed, before we behaved, if we do, we were already someone to Him.

09:06.835 --> 09:10.420
Christ died for us while we were still in sin.

09:12.022 --> 09:13.804
He didn't die for us after we'd got it together.

09:13.824 --> 09:15.887
He died for us before we got it together.

09:16.948 --> 09:18.450
Now, give me a little wave if you

09:18.562 --> 09:21.225
You know Jesus as your personal Lord and Savior.

09:21.786 --> 09:22.487
Just give me a little wave.

09:22.867 --> 09:26.132
If you don't, you're gonna have an opportunity in a few minutes to do that.

09:27.173 --> 09:27.413
Okay?

09:29.115 --> 09:37.946
But because you and I have been redeemed, our responsibility, if you waved at me right then, is to introduce other people to the Redeemer.

09:39.048 --> 09:40.329
So if you were, give me another wave.

09:41.230 --> 09:42.032
It's less hands now.

09:45.596 --> 09:47.218
If you have been redeemed,

09:47.554 --> 09:59.230
If you've been bought with a price, if you know that your name is in the Lamb's Book of Life, you and I now have a responsibility to jump out of that bubble which we live in and introduce people to Jesus.

10:00.832 --> 10:11.667
I believe every person on earth, every person at University of East Anglia at the Art College in your high school, every person in our world deserves to know that they are someone.

10:13.029 --> 10:13.589
Every person.

10:14.531 --> 10:16.914
We are all equal to Jesus.

10:17.794 --> 10:21.519
Now, we are not all children of God, but we are all loved by God.

10:23.201 --> 10:25.343
A child of God is someone who calls God a father.

10:26.224 --> 10:30.109
So if you call God your father, you, he is your child, we are children of God.

10:30.790 --> 10:32.793
But God loves everyone.

10:33.634 --> 10:38.880
God loves every single person sitting in this room and watching online.

10:39.521 --> 10:40.602
Now, I want to ask another question.

10:40.722 --> 10:46.930
Who would agree every person you know who doesn't know Jesus would live a vastly better life if they did?

10:48.226 --> 10:48.627
Three of us.

10:51.631 --> 10:53.714
Whose life is better for meeting Jesus?

10:56.899 --> 10:57.940
Beth was singing that song.

10:57.980 --> 11:01.405
I was thinking that those words, I'm not going to get them right because I'm not the worship leader.

11:01.706 --> 11:03.829
That's not my job to get the words of the worship songs, right?

11:04.209 --> 11:06.092
My job is to interpret what I heard.

11:08.816 --> 11:14.525
But there was a line in that song thinking about something like, just to think of what had been if I had not met him or not been.

11:14.585 --> 11:15.506
What was it, Chantel?

11:16.546 --> 11:17.487
You've been so, so good.

11:17.527 --> 11:18.249
See, just like that.

11:19.370 --> 11:24.638
Basically, if we hadn't have met Jesus, can you even fathom where you'd be right now?

11:25.339 --> 11:27.322
Someone said to me recently, you could have been in prison, John.

11:27.823 --> 11:28.644
I was like, that's kind.

11:33.091 --> 11:33.612
How kind?

11:36.496 --> 11:40.262
But the question is, where would we be if we hadn't have met Jesus?

11:42.024 --> 11:45.810
Because everybody is someone and someone

11:46.242 --> 11:47.604
matters to Jesus.

11:48.826 --> 11:55.276
And if we recognize that everyone is someone, it's actually going to change the way we view the person at work who annoys us.

11:57.699 --> 12:06.232
It's actually going to change the way we view people in life because it's amazing you can actually build prejudices up against people because we live in bubbles.

12:08.115 --> 12:10.739
I'm going to say some challenging things today because I want to challenge this.

12:10.759 --> 12:15.506
I want to try and broaden our thinking, but I believe in border control and I believe in safe borders.

12:16.002 --> 12:22.592
And I do not have answers to all the illegal immigration issues in the crisis that our nation and other nations are facing right now.

12:23.233 --> 12:32.066
What I do know is this, they are someone's son, someone's father, and they are someone deeply loved and someone that Christ died for.

12:37.033 --> 12:45.906
Now we have to understand that every person, every creed, every color, every religion is someone that Christ

12:46.018 --> 12:46.599
died for.

12:47.920 --> 12:48.640
Christ died for.

12:49.842 --> 12:55.647
We might not see them as someone, but we have to see through his eyes they are someone.

12:56.668 --> 13:10.521
And this one thought can actually change everything because when someone annoys me, frustrates me, upsets me, cuts me up on the road, on the way to church, sends you crazy emails, sends me crazy emails.

13:11.602 --> 13:11.962
You ready?

13:13.664 --> 13:15.986
Everyone is someone

13:16.386 --> 13:17.367
that Christ died for.

13:19.731 --> 13:21.433
Do you just, should you hold that thought for a second?

13:22.755 --> 13:26.099
Everyone is someone that Christ died for.

13:27.421 --> 13:30.546
You see, it's easy to go on mission if you love the person that God's called you to reach.

13:33.690 --> 13:38.436
It's easy if that person is the same political stance, the same viewpoint of life, the same value system.

13:38.456 --> 13:43.323
They're actually easy, but what about if God's called you to reach someone who's actually really unlovable?

13:44.224 --> 13:45.426
What about if they're unlikable?

13:46.786 --> 13:51.911
What about if God's cause you to love someone that you don't want to?

13:55.554 --> 13:59.918
What about when we want to give someone a piece of our minds, but we remember there's someone?

14:01.580 --> 14:10.128
Society, even your own family might label you a misfit or a nobody or an addict, but God doesn't see you as an addict or a misfit or a nobody.

14:10.248 --> 14:16.594
God sees you as someone, someone that he went to the cross for.

14:18.466 --> 14:26.160
And I think we can actually change our paradigm if we know that everyone is someone and that someone is my mission.

14:27.482 --> 14:32.671
Because God is going to place some people across your past this year that maybe aren't even nice.

14:34.014 --> 14:36.498
Maybe that God is calling you to reach some people who

14:37.474 --> 14:40.739
They don't agree with you coming to church, or they've said some things about the church.

14:40.779 --> 14:45.987
They've said some unkind things about other races, religions, and God said, you are now my instrument.

14:46.307 --> 14:51.755
You are now on mission to share the love of Jesus to this hurting, dying world.

14:53.438 --> 14:58.385
And I think if we can change our paradigm, I think we have the potential to make a difference in our city.

14:59.166 --> 15:02.491
The person who is of a different faith, political stance, is someone.

15:03.353 --> 15:07.058
The family member who betrayed you lied to you, stole from you,

15:07.426 --> 15:09.429
is someone.

15:09.449 --> 15:16.779
The homeless person that you walk past every morning in a rush to get to work is someone, someone with a story.

15:19.863 --> 15:25.872
The person at the checkout at the supermarket who grunts when you say good morning is someone.

15:26.693 --> 15:28.736
Well, if they're not going to say good morning, I'm not going to say it next time.

15:32.942 --> 15:36.146
Come on, we've all had these things.

15:36.674 --> 15:43.041
Jesus teaches us to love, to turn the other cheek, to go the extra mile.

15:44.623 --> 15:48.307
What Jesus teaches is often completely opposite to our feelings.

15:50.230 --> 15:57.858
But I want to remind us today on mission that everyone is someone and that someone matters to Christ.

15:59.060 --> 16:04.466
We could have our opinions, our objections, our concerns, and I have them, but they're still someone.

16:05.698 --> 16:14.568
I wonder if the thought that everybody is someone could break through the prejudices and the disunities that we hold around each other.

16:15.189 --> 16:21.757
That someone might dress look different, look different, appear different, smell different, talk different, identify different.

16:21.777 --> 16:28.224
They might even make you feel uncomfortable, but they are someone.

16:28.244 --> 16:29.145
They are someone.

16:29.746 --> 16:33.490
And that someone is the person which Christ died for.

16:35.874 --> 16:37.176
I've never known it so quiet.

16:40.360 --> 16:42.523
They're the someone who Jesus loves.

16:44.305 --> 16:48.370
The person who drives you crazy in church, and when you see them come in, you go, I'm going that side.

16:50.393 --> 16:52.115
The person who you want to cancel.

16:53.377 --> 16:56.160
The president or prime minister or leader, you can't stand.

16:56.961 --> 16:58.003
And maybe for good reason.

16:59.605 --> 17:03.570
Can you imagine if we made a decision instead of

17:03.810 --> 17:10.018
pointing a finger or judging, we exchange that for praying for them.

17:10.038 --> 17:11.260
We all have our thoughts and opinions.

17:11.280 --> 17:19.310
I'm just saying, can you imagine if we exchange this week, every time they appeared on television in the press, we said, right now, I pray right now.

17:20.532 --> 17:20.992
I pray.

17:21.333 --> 17:25.378
The Bible says, instructs us to pray for kings and queens and presidents and leaders.

17:25.679 --> 17:31.346
Imagine if we exchanged our blogs for prayers, our frustration for prayer.

17:34.850 --> 17:36.472
I wonder how different our world would be.

17:36.493 --> 17:40.118
It doesn't excuse the behavior of leaders.

17:40.158 --> 17:41.560
That's not what I'm talking about.

17:43.483 --> 17:48.952
Talking about maybe the mission of God is different to what we first thought.

17:51.295 --> 17:56.543
Sometimes God's calling us to love the ones we don't want to love.

17:58.146 --> 17:59.007
Who is your someone?

18:00.169 --> 18:03.634
Who is the person that God's called you to reach?

18:04.130 --> 18:04.591
in 2026.

18:07.137 --> 18:12.189
Maybe it seems impossible that they would even receive the love.

18:12.931 --> 18:15.999
What prayer does is prayer softens a heart.

18:17.362 --> 18:20.690
So when you pray for someone, what it does is it softens their heart.

18:20.834 --> 18:24.279
So when you talk to them, the heart is ready for them to receive.

18:24.839 --> 18:32.310
If you go and speak to someone on mission without praying first, the heart is so hard, they will not be able to receive the seed, so they reject it.

18:32.610 --> 18:40.881
But when you pray, I've proven this so many times, when I pray, when I go into chaplaincy every Friday, this is my prayer.

18:40.901 --> 18:43.545
Lord, soften the hearts of the players and the coaches.

18:43.805 --> 18:47.490
So when I speak to them, their hearts are soft to receive the words that I speak.

18:47.851 --> 18:50.354
If you go on mission without prayer,

18:50.594 --> 18:52.817
It's full on dead soil.

18:53.258 --> 18:58.005
This is why the omission which Pete spoke about last week is so important.

18:58.966 --> 19:04.134
What if God is calling us to befriend someone who doesn't look like us, dress like us, appear like us?

19:04.414 --> 19:09.983
What if God is calling us to invite someone to church this year and we don't even like them?

19:13.147 --> 19:15.010
Well, no, I don't want them to come.

19:15.911 --> 19:17.714
I'll recommend a church down the road.

19:20.162 --> 19:23.227
I see them Monday to Friday, the thought of seeing them on my day off.

19:24.709 --> 19:26.592
What about if God was stirring our hearts?

19:28.134 --> 19:31.619
Because everybody is someone who Christ died for.

19:32.661 --> 19:34.263
God sees them by name.

19:34.604 --> 19:36.547
Isaiah 43, once is, do not fear.

